# Understanding the Code

## `main()`

```dart
void main() {
  runApp(const BloodReportApp());
}
```

Every Flutter app starts here.

`runApp()` launches the application.

---

## `MaterialApp`

This is the root of your application.

It controls:

* App title
* Theme
* Navigation
* Initial screen

---

## `theme`

We set the primary color to red because it's related to blood and healthcare.

We'll improve the design later.

---

## `home`

```dart
home: const SplashScreen(),
```

This tells Flutter:

> "When the app starts, show the Splash Screen."

---

## `Scaffold`

A `Scaffold` is the basic page structure.

Think of it as the canvas for each screen.

Every major screen in our app will use a `Scaffold`.

---

